INTITIAL PROMPT

I run a financial services firm with hundreds of financial advisors.  I am looking to build a tool that helps us present various income interruption events to show the gap that exists when an event occurs.  The events are Unemployment, Illness or Injury, Death, and Lawsuit.  I would like each of these events to be demonstrated on different modules.  There should be a Home Screen that allows me to enter the client’s personal data, including age of each income earner and their individual incomes, current Group Long-term Disability (GLTD), Private Disability (IDI), Group Life Insurance (GLI), Private Life Insurance (Life) that is either Term or Permanent, and Liability Limits for Home/Auto.  Each module then should have a bar chart of “income over time” showing their income increasing 3% per year until retirement age of 65.  The bar chart should show what total income is while factoring in lost income due to a presumed event.  The Injury or Illness module should factor in GLTD and IDI showing any gap that may exist. The Death Module should factor in the GLI to age 65 while Term insurance is for the length of the term, and assumes an investment rate of return of 5% when utilizing the death benefit as income replacement.  The Lawsuit module should factor in a maximum wage garnishment of 25% every year until age 65 and the total garnishment minus the current liability limits is the Liability Gap.  The Unemployment module should assume their current monthly income multiplied by 3 months and 6 months and show these two numbers as the High and Low ranges for their Emergency Reserve Savings bucket.  Our firm’s name is North Star Resource Group and our logos and branding are included.

